    {
      "number": 10,
      "id": "I_kwDOMm_Q2s6VnxZC",
      "title": "sd_hash in issued CWT? issuer includes all possible disclosures?",
      "url": "https://github.com/ietf-wg-spice/draft-ietf-spice-sd-cwt/issues/10",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "rohanmahy",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "currently the sd_hash claim in an SD-CWT is allowed when sent between an issuer and the holder. This is a claim which could not be verified by a verifier. I propose we remove it. If instead the Issuer is required to send salted claim disclosures for every digest in the payload (already proposed in PR #9 ), then the holder has another way of detecting tapering of the unprotected header. \r\n\r\nwe also need confidentiality of the disclosures. the most common ways (ex: transport crypto, authenticated encryption of the entire SD-CWT) also provide additional integrity protection of the unprotected header between an issuer and a holder",
      "createdAt": "2024-09-06T11:35:31Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-09-06T11:40:25Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 11,
      "id": "I_kwDOMm_Q2s6Vnz3a",
      "title": "Support Decoy Digests",
      "url": "https://github.com/ietf-wg-spice/draft-ietf-spice-sd-cwt/issues/11",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "rohanmahy",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "do we want to support decoy digests like SD-JWT does?\r\n\r\nIf so, I left a simple hook to do so in PR #9 ",
      "createdAt": "2024-09-06T11:41:52Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-09-06T11:41:52Z",
