    {
      "number": 12,
      "id": "I_kwDOMm_Q2s6Vn1_n",
      "title": "Can you have an SD-CWT with no blinded claims",
      "url": "https://github.com/ietf-wg-spice/draft-ietf-spice-sd-cwt/issues/12",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "rohanmahy",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "is a zebra with no stripes still a zebra? \r\n\r\nlikewise is it legal to have an SD-CWT with no blinded claims. shouldn't that just be a regular CWT?\r\n\r\nIt is easier to talk about what various roles have to do with this requirement. Is there a good reason to allow a CWT with `typ` \"application/sd-cwt\" that has no blinded claims?\r\n\r\nNote that PR #9 currently assumes an SD-CWT needs at least one blinded claim.",
      "createdAt": "2024-09-06T11:47:09Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-09-06T11:47:09Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    }
